HEADWORD: Unbrace
<hw>Un*brace"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>brace</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from tension; to
relax; to loose; <as>as, to <ex>unbrace</ex> a drum; to <ex>unbrace</ex>
the nerves</as>.</def> <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbraid</ent>⟦br⟧
